ğŸ§© Part 1: The Group Policy CLI

ğŸ”¹ Step 1: gpupdate

Command used to review syntax and options:

gpupdate /?


Command to force update of all Group Policy settings:

gpupdate /force

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: gpresult

Command to review syntax and options:

gpresult /?


Command to display the Resultant Set of Policy (RSoP) summary data:

gpresult /R


Command to save the report in HTML format:

gpresult /H GPReport.html

ğŸ§© Part 2: The net command
ğŸ”¹ Step 1: net user

Command to review syntax and options:

net user /?


Command to list all user accounts on the computer:

net user


Command to view settings for a specific user (example ITEUser):

net user ITEUser


Command to add a new user (with admin privileges):

net user User1 ITEPassword /add

â“ When does the password expire?

âœ… Answer:

Never


Command to delete the user account:

net user User1 /delete
